Vaginal structure (body structure)
Genital System, Female, Vagina
Vagina, NOS
VAGINA
Vagina
vagina""" ;
                                                            :definition "The female genital canal, extending from the uterus to the vulva." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12407" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Vagina" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12408
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12408> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13018> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """External Genitalia
female pudendum
mammalian vulva
puboperineal region
pudendum femininum
Vulval structure (body structure)
VULVA
Vulva
Vulva, NOS
vulva""" ;
                                                            :definition "The external, visible part of the female genitalia surrounding the urethral and vaginal opening. The vulva includes the clitoris and inner as well as outer labia." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12408" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Vulva" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12409
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12409> rdf:type owl:Class ;
