BODY CAVITY, NASAL
olfactory chamber cavity
cavity of nose
cavity of olfactory apparatus
nasal conduit space
nasal cavity
Nasal cavity
Nasal cavity structure (body structure)""" ;
                                                            :definition "The proximal portion of the respiratory passages on either side of the nasal septum lying between the floor of the cranium and the roof of the mouth and extending from the face to the pharynx. The nasal cavity is lined with ciliated mucosa, extending from the nares to the pharynx." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12424" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Nasal Cavity" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12426
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12426> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12712> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """Head and Neck, Salivary Glands
Major salivary gland, NOS
SALIVARY GLAND
Salivary Gland
Salivary Glands
salivary gland
GLAND, SALIVARY""" ;
                                                            :definition "An exocrine gland that secretes saliva. Salivary glands are mostly located in and around the oral cavity." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12426" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Salivary Gland" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12428
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12428> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13018> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """cartilaginous trachea
Tracheal structure (body structure)
vertebrate trachea
TRACHEA
Trachea
Windpipe
trachea
windpipe""" ;
                                                            :definition "The fibrocartilaginous, mucous-lined tube passing from the larynx to the bronchi." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12428" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Trachea" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12431
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12431> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13018> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """medulla ossea
bone marrow
Bone marrow
medulla ossium
Bone marrow structure (body structure)
Bone Marrow
Reticuloendothelial System, Bone Marrow
BONE MARROW
Marrow""" ;
                                                            :definition "The tissue occupying the spaces of bone. It consists of blood vessel sinuses and a network of hematopoietic cells which give rise to the red cells, white cells, and megakaryocytes." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12431" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Bone Marrow" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12432
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12432> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13018> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """Reticuloendothelial System, Spleen
Splenic structure (body structure)
SPLEEN
Spleen
Splenic
spleen
splenic""" ;
                                                            :definition "An organ that is part of the hematopoietic and immune systems. It is composed of the white pulp and the red pulp and is surrounded by a capsule. It is located in the left hypochondriac region. Its functions include lymphocyte production, blood cell storage, and blood cell destruction." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12432" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Spleen" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12433
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12433> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13018> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """thymus gland
thymus organ
Thymus gland structure (body structure)
Thymus Gland
Reticuloendothelial System, Thymus
THYMUS GLAND
THYMUS
Thymus
thymus""" ;
                                                            :definition "A bi-lobed organ surrounded by a connective tissue capsule. It is located in the upper anterior portion of the chest, behind the sternum. It is composed predominantly of lymphocytes and fewer epithelial cells. Connective tissue septa separate the lobes into lobules. The lobules contain an outer portion (cortical zone) which is rich in lymphocytes and an inner portion (medullary zone) which is rich in epithelial cells. It is an organ essential for the development of the immune system. Its function is the maturation of the progenitor lymphoid cells to thymocytes and subsequently to mature T-cells. It reaches its greatest weight at puberty and subsequently begins to involute." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12433" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Thymus Gland" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12434
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12434> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13236> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """peripheral blood
vertebrate blood
Reticuloendothelial System, Blood
Peripheral Blood
portion of blood
Whole Blood
BLOOD
Blood
blood""" ;
                                                            :definition "A liquid tissue; its major function is to transport oxygen throughout the body. It also supplies the tissues with nutrients, removes waste products, and contains various components of the immune system defending the body against infection. Several hormones also travel in the blood." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12434" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Blood" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12439
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12439> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13018> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """Nervous System, Brain
Brain structure (body structure)
BRAIN
Brain
Brain, NOS
CNS-Brain
brain""" ;
                                                            :definition "An organ composed of grey and white matter containing billions of neurons that is the center for intelligence and reasoning. It is protected by the bony cranium." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12439" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Brain" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12464
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12464> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13018> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """Spinal cord
spinal cord
Spinal Cord
Medulla Spinalis
Spinal cord structure (body structure)
SPINAL CORD""" ;
                                                            :definition "The elongated, approximately cylindrical part of the central nervous system of vertebrates that lies in the vertebral canal and from which the spinal nerves emerge." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12464" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Spinal Cord" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12468
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12468> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13018> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """Lung structure (body structure)
Respiratory System, Lung
LUNG
Lung
Lung, NOS
Lungs
lung
pulmo""" ;
                                                            :definition "One of a pair of viscera occupying the pulmonary cavities of the thorax, the organs of respiration in which aeration of the blood takes place. As a rule, the right lung is slightly larger than the left and is divided into three lobes (an upper, a middle, and a lower or basal), while the left has two lobes (an upper and a lower or basal). Each lung is irregularly conical in shape, presenting a blunt upper extremity (the apex), a concave base following the curve of the diaphragm, an outer convex surface (costal surface), an inner or mediastinal surface (mediastinal surface), a thin and sharp anterior border, and a thick and rounded posterior border." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12468" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Lung" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12470
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12470> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13018> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """entire skin
Skin structure (body structure)
skin of body
Skin, total
Human Skin
Integument
SKIN
Skin
Skin, NOS
skin organ""" ;
                                                            :definition "An organ that constitutes the external surface of the body. It consists of the epidermis, dermis, and skin appendages." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12470" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Skin" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12487
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12487> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12913> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """Signet Ring Cell
Signet-Ring Cell""" ;
                                                            :definition "A neoplastic cell containing cytoplasmic mucin. The presence of mucin pushes the nucleus of the cell to the periphery, assuming a configuration resembling a signet ring." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12487" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Signet Ring Cell" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C125189
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C125189> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                             rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C13321> ;
                                                             :Synonyms """Alimentary Bolus
Bolus of Ingested Food
Bolus of Food
Bolus""" ;
                                                             :definition "A soft mass or lump of chewed food that is passed from the mouth into the esophagus and the stomach." ;
                                                             :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C125189" ;
                                                             rdfs:label "Alimentary Bolus" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C125896
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C125896> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                             rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12712> ;
                                                             :Synonyms """Anal Sac
SAC, ANAL""" ;
                                                             :definition "Paired glands located on either side of the anus of most carnivores that secrete a noxious-smelling liquid, thus allowing members of the same species to identify one another." ;
                                                             :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C125896" ;
                                                             rdfs:label "Anal Sac" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12607
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12607> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12913> ;
                                                            :Synonyms """Multinucleated Giant Cell
MULTINUCLEATED GIANT CELL
Giant Cell
syncytium""" ;
                                                            :definition "An abnormally large cell that contains multiple nuclei and an abundant amount of cytoplasm." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12607" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Giant Cell" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C126083
