                                                            :Synonyms """Tissue
tissue
Tissues
tissues
TISSUE""" ;
                                                            :definition "An anatomical structure consisting of similarly specialized cells and intercellular matrix, aggregated according to genetically determined spatical relationships, performing a specific function." ;
                                                            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12801" ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Tissue" .


