Red Blood Cells, Rejuvenated, Frozen, Deglycerolized
Red Blood Cells Rejuvenated Frozen Deglycerolized""" ;
                                                             :definition "Red blood cells treated with a rejuvenating solution, then frozen using a cryoprotective agent, and finally, washed free of the rejuvenating solution and glycerol." ;
                                                             :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C133355" ;
                                                             rdfs:label "Rejuvenated, Frozen, Deglycerolized Red Blood Cells" .


###  http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C133356
