Anesthetic Agent
Anaesthetics
Anaesthetic Agent
Anesthetic Drugs
Anesthetic
anesthetic""" ;
                  :definition "A pharmacological agent that acts in a reversible fashion and can be applied either locally or systemically to cause a partial or total loss of sensation and pain or to induce unconsciousness." ;
                  :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C245" ;
                  rdfs:label "Anesthetic Agent" .


