                                               :Observation ;
                               :Synonyms """Delayed Capillary Refill
Delayed Capillary Refill Time""" ;
                               :definition "A clinical finding in which a capillary nail refill test returns to pink color in greater than two seconds after pressure is removed." ;
                               :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C168181" ;
                               rdfs:label "Delayed Capillary Refill Time" .


