                                   :Synonyms """Extracellular Matrix Protein Gene
ECM Protein Gene""" ;
                                   :definition "Extracellular Matrix Protein Genes encode mostly fibrous Extracellular Matrix Proteins (e.g., Collagen, Elastin, Fibronectins, and Laminin), typically located in the Extracellular Matrix and commonly involved in cell attachment, cell movement, cell growth, morphogenesis, organogenesis, and tissue repair, architecture, and organization." ;
                                   :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C26000" ;
                                   rdfs:label "Extracellular Matrix Protein Gene" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Extracorporeal_Membrane_Oxygenation
:Extracorporeal_Membrane_Oxygenation rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                     rdfs:subClassOf :Respiratory_Therapy ;
                                     :Synonyms """Extracorporeal Life Supports
Venovenous Extracorporeal Membrane Oxygenation
Oxygenation, Extracorporeal Membrane
ECLS Treatment
Venoarterial ECMOs
ECMO Treatment
ECMO Extracorporeal Membrane Oxygenation
Venoarterial Extracorporeal Membrane Oxygenation
Membrane Oxygenation, Extracorporeal
Life Support, Extracorporeal
Extracorporeal Life Support
Extracorporeal Membrane Oxygenations
Treatment, ECMO
ECLS Treatments
Treatment, ECLS
ECMO, Venoarterial
Venovenous ECMO
Venoarterial ECMO
ECMO, Venovenous
ECMO Treatments
Venovenous ECMOs""" ;
                                     :definition "Application of a life support system that circulates the blood through an oxygenating system, which may consist of a pump, a membrane oxygenator, and a heat exchanger. Examples of its use are to assist victims of SMOKE INHALATION INJURY; RESPIRATORY FAILURE; and CARDIAC FAILURE." ;
                                     :reference "http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/MESH/D015199" ;
                                     rdfs:label "Extracorporeal Membrane Oxygenation" .


