HR
Heart Rate
Heart rate""" ;
            :definition "The number of heartbeats per unit of time, usually expressed as beats per minute." ;
            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C49677" ;
            rdfs:label "Heart Rate" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Heat_Shock_Protein
:Heat_Shock_Protein rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf :Protein_Family ;
                    :Synonyms """stress protein
Heat Shock Protein
Heat Shock Proteins
heat-shock protein
HSP""" ;
                    :definition "A family of highly-conserved proteins that are synthesized in response to hyperthermia (heat shock), hypoxia, or other stresses that appear to increase cellular thermal tolerance and enable cells to recover from stress. Some heat shock proteins may protect other proteins from denaturation, degradation or perform functions essential to cell survival under these conditions." ;
                    :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C16672" ;
                    rdfs:label "Heat Shock Protein" .


