Immune disorder, NOS
Immune Dysfunction
Unspecified Immune System Problem
Immune System Disorder
Immunologic Disorder
Immune Disorder""" ;
                        :definition "A disorder resulting from an abnormality in the immune system." ;
                        :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C3507" ;
                        rdfs:label "Immune System Disorder" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Immunization
:Immunization rdf:type owl:Class ;
              rdfs:subClassOf :Public_Health_Practice ;
              :Synonyms """Immunostimulation
Immunological Stimulations
Sensitization, Immunologic
Sensitizations, Immunological
Sensitization, Immunological
Stimulation, Immunological
Immunologic Sensitization
Variolation
Immunological Sensitization
Stimulation, Immunologic
Stimulations, Immunological
Immunizations
Immunological Stimulation
Immunological Sensitizations
Immunologic Stimulation
Variolations""" ;
              :definition "Deliberate stimulation of the host's immune response. ACTIVE IMMUNIZATION involves administration of ANTIGENS or IMMUNOLOGIC ADJUVANTS. PASSIVE IMMUNIZATION involves administration of IMMUNE SERA or LYMPHOCYTES or their extracts (e.g., transfer factor, immune RNA) or transplantation of immunocompetent cell producing tissue (thymus or bone marrow)." ;
              :reference "http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/MESH/D007114" ;
              rdfs:label "Immunization" .


