:Interleukin rdf:type owl:Class ;
             rdfs:subClassOf :Cytokine ;
             :Synonyms """Interleukin
interleukin
Interleukins
IL""" ;
             :definition "Interleukin is the generic name for a group of well-characterized cytokines that are produced by leukocytes and other cell types. They have a broad spectrum of functional activities that regulate the activities and capabilities of a wide variety of cell types. They are particularly important as members of the cytokine networks that regulate inflammatory and immune responses." ;
