Ligand Binding Protein""" ;
                        :definition "General term for proteins that have binding as a major function." ;
                        :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C17728" ;
                        rdfs:label "Ligand Binding Protein" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Ligand_Binding_Protein_Gene
:Ligand_Binding_Protein_Gene rdf:type owl:Class ;
                             rdfs:subClassOf <http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C16612> ;
                             :Synonyms "Ligand Binding Protein Gene" ;
                             :definition "Ligand Binding Protein Genes encode Ligand Binding Proteins, a large class of diverse proteins for which a major function appears to be (typically high affinity) binding of some ligand for solubility, transport, bioactivity regulation, or other nonenzymatic process. Ligand interaction often alters protein molecular conformation and function." ;
                             :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C21295" ;
                             rdfs:label "Ligand Binding Protein Gene" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#LightCycler_SeptiFast
:LightCycler_SeptiFast rdf:type owl:Class ;
                       rdfs:subClassOf :Adult_Sepsis_Diagnostic_Biomarker ;
                       :Synonyms "LightCycler SeptiFast" ;
                       :definition "LightCycler SeptiFast, a multipathogen probe-based real-time polymerase chain reaction, in the rapid etiological diagnosis of sepsis in patients with clinical and laboratory signs of bloodstream infections." ;
                       :reference "Avolio M, Diamante P, Modolo ML, De Rosa R, Stano P, Camporese A. Direct molecular detection of pathogens in blood as specific rule-in diagnostic biomarker in patients with presumed sepsis: our experience on a heterogeneous cohort of patients with signs of infective systemic inflammatory response syndrome. Shock. 2014 Aug;42(2):86-92. doi: 10.1097/SHK.0000000000000191. PMID: 24727869." ;
                       rdfs:label "LightCycler SeptiFast" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Lincomycin
:Lincomycin rdf:type owl:Class ;
            rdfs:subClassOf :Lincosamide_Antibiotic .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Lincosamide_Antibiotic
:Lincosamide_Antibiotic rdf:type owl:Class ;
                        rdfs:subClassOf :Antibiotic ;
                        :Synonyms "Lincosamide Antibiotic" ;
                        :definition "Any synthetic or semi-synthetic derivative of lincomycin, first isolated from a soil actinomycete Streptomyces lincolnensis, with antibacterial activity. Lincosamide antibiotics bind to the 23S rRNA in the large 50S subunit of bacterial ribosomes, thereby preventing the peptidyl-tRNA translocation from the A site to the P site. This results in peptidyl-tRNA dissociation from ribosomes, and leads to the release of incomplete proteins, ultimately causing cell death." ;
                        :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C82922" ;
                        rdfs:label "Lincosamide Antibiotic" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Lipid_Measurement
:Lipid_Measurement rdf:type owl:Class ;
                   rdfs:subClassOf :Chemistry_Test ;
                   :Synonyms """Total Lipid
Lipid Measurement
LIPID
Lipid""" ;
                   :definition "A quantitative measurement of the amount of lipids (cholesterol, lipoproteins, and triglycerides) present in a sample." ;
                   :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C74949" ;
                   rdfs:label "Lipid Measurement" .


