MAPK""" ;
                 :definition "MAP kinase gene products act as an integration point for multiple biochemical signals, and are involved in a wide variety of cellular processes such as proliferation, differentiation, transcription regulation and development." ;
                 :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C26360" ;
                 rdfs:label "MAP Kinase Gene" .


