###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Patient_Isolation
:Patient_Isolation rdf:type owl:Class ;
                   rdfs:subClassOf :Infection_Control ;
                   :Synonyms "Negative Pressure Patient Isolation" ;
                   :definition "The segregation of patients with communicable or other diseases for a specified time. Isolation may be strict, in which movement and social contacts are limited; modified, where an effort to control specified aspects of care is made in order to prevent cross infection; or reverse, where the patient is secluded in a controlled or germ-free environment in order to protect him or her from cross infection." ;
                   :reference "http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/MESH/D010356" ;
                   rdfs:label "Patient Isolation" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Peak_Systolic_Blood_Velocity
