###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Riker_Sedation-Agitation_Scale_Clinical_Classification
:Riker_Sedation-Agitation_Scale_Clinical_Classification rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                        rdfs:subClassOf :Sedation_Assessment ;
                                                        :Synonyms """Riker Sedation-Agitation Scale Clinical Classification
SAS
SAS01""" ;
                                                        :definition "A standardized seven-point rating scale developed by Riker et al. 1999 to assess the level of alertness and agitation in critically ill patients. The assigned score ranges from 1 to 7, with three levels of sedation ranging from unarousable to sedated, one level indicating calm and cooperative, and three levels of agitation, ranging from agitated to dangerous agitation." ;
                                                        :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C171418" ;
                                                        rdfs:label "Riker Sedation-Agitation Scale Clinical Classification" .


