###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Septic_Shock
:Septic_Shock rdf:type owl:Class ;
              rdfs:subClassOf :Complication ,
                              :Shock ;
              :Synonyms """Septic Shock
Systemic Septic Shock""" ;
              :definition "Septic shock is a subset of sepsis in which underlying circulatory and cellular/metabolic abnormalities are profound enough to substantially increase mortality." ;
              :reference "Singer M, Deutschman CS, Seymour CW, Shankar-Hari M, Annane D, Bauer M, Bellomo R, Bernard GR, Chiche JD, Coopersmith CM, Hotchkiss RS, Levy MM, Marshall JC, Martin GS, Opal SM, Rubenfeld GD, van der Poll T, Vincent JL, Angus DC. The Third International Consensus Definitions for Sepsis and Septic Shock (Sepsis-3). JAMA. 2016 Feb 23;315(8):801-10. doi: 10.1001/jama.2016.0287. PMID: 26903338; PMCID: PMC4968574." ,
                         "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C35018" ;
              rdfs:label "Septic Shock" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Sequential_Organ_Failure_Assessment
