                                                     :Adult_Sepsis_Prognostic_Biomarker ,
                                                     :Diagnostic_Criteria ,
                                                     :Neonatal_Sepsis_Prognostic_Biomarker ,
                                                     :Paediatric_Sepsis_Prognostic_Biomarker ;
                                     :Synonyms """SOFA
Sequential Organ Failure Assessment""" ;
                                     :definition "A diagnostic criteria for sepsis." ;
                                     :reference "Singer M, Deutschman CS, Seymour CW, Shankar-Hari M, Annane D, Bauer M, Bellomo R, Bernard GR, Chiche JD, Coopersmith CM, Hotchkiss RS, Levy MM, Marshall JC, Martin GS, Opal SM, Rubenfeld GD, van der Poll T, Vincent JL, Angus DC. The Third International Consensus Definitions for Sepsis and Septic Shock (Sepsis-3). JAMA. 2016 Feb 23;315(8):801-10. doi: 10.1001/jama.2016.0287. PMID: 26903338; PMCID: PMC4968574." ,
                                                "http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/SNOMEDCT/459231000124102" ;
                                     rdfs:label "Sequential Organ Failure Assessment" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Serine_Protease
:Serine_Protease rdf:type owl:Class ;
                 rdfs:subClassOf :Peptidase ;
                 :Synonyms """Serine Proteinase
Serine Protease
Serine Peptidase""" ;
                 :definition "Proteases that have a serine residue in the active center of the enzyme. These enzymes catalyze the hydrolysis of covalent peptidic bonds by serine nucleophilic attack. Serine proteases participate in a wide range of functions in the body, including blood clotting, inflammation, and digestion." ;
                 :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C17123" ;
                 rdfs:label "Serine Protease" .


