###  http://www.semanticweb.org/zchero/ontologies/2023/11/SepsisOntology#Sulfonamide_Anti-Infective_Agent
:Sulfonamide_Anti-Infective_Agent rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf :Antibiotic ;
                                  :Synonyms """Sulfonamides
Sulfonamide Anti-Infective Agent
sulfonamide
sulfa drug""" ;
                                  :definition "A class of natural or synthetic sulfanilamide derivatives with antibacterial activity. Sulfonamides are structural analogs of para-aminobenzoic acid (essential for microbial folate synthesis). Sulfonamides inhibit bacterial metabolism by competing with PABA for dihydropteroate synthase, thereby resulting in disruption of folic acid metabolism and ultimately DNA synthesis." ;
                                  :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C29739" ;
                                  rdfs:label "Sulfonamide Anti-Infective Agent" .


