CYSTM1""" ;
                                                 :definition "A protein coding gene CYSTM1 in human." ;
                                                 :reference "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HGNC_30239" ;
                                                 rdfs:label "Cysteine-rich Transmembrane Module Containing 1" .


:Cytochrome_P450_1B1 :Synonyms """EC 1.14.14.1
Cytochrome P450 1B1
CYP1B1
CYPIB1""" ;
                     :definition "Cytochrome P450 1B1 (543 aa, ~61 kDa) is encoded by the human CYP1B1 gene. This protein plays a role in the metabolism of steroids and xenobiotics." ;
                     :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C104237" ;
                     rdfs:label "Cytochrome P450 1B1" .


:DLL1_Gene :Synonyms """Delta-Like 1 (Drosophila) Gene
DLL1
DLL1 Gene""" ;
           :definition "This gene is involved in notch signaling." ;
           :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C106582" ;
           rdfs:label "DLL1 Gene" .


:DPP4_Gene :Synonyms """Dipeptidyl-Peptidase 4 Gene
DPP4
DPP4 Gene""" ;
           :definition "This gene is involved in the regulation of proteolysis." ;
           :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C91298" ;
           rdfs:label "DPP4 Gene" .


:Dabigatran :Synonyms """DABIGATRAN
Dabigatran""" ;
            :definition "A benzimidazole and direct thrombin inhibitor, with anticoagulant activity. Upon administration, dabigatran reversibly binds to and inhibits the activity of thrombin, a serine protease that converts fibrinogen into fibrin. This disrupts the coagulation cascade and inhibits the formation of blood clots." ;
            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C73224" ;
            rdfs:label "Dabigatran" .


:Dalteparin :Synonyms """DALTEPARIN
Dalteparin
dalteparin""" ;
            :definition "A low molecular weight, synthetic heparin. As an anticoagulant/antithrombotic agent, dalteparin binds to antithrombin and enhances the inhibition of Factor Xa. Compared to unfractionated heparins, the use of dalteparin is associated with lower incidences of osteoporosis and heparin-induced thrombocytopenia." ;
            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C1453" ;
            rdfs:label "Dalteparin" .


:Delta-like_1 :Synonyms """Delta-like Protein 1
DLL1""" ;
              :definition "A protein coding gene DLL1 in human." ;
              :reference "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HGNC_2908" ;
              rdfs:label "Delta-like Protein 1" .


