:Fentanyl :Synonyms """N-(1-phenethylpiperidin-4-yl)-N-phenylpropionamide
Abstral
Duragesic
FENTANYL
Fentanyl""" ;
          :definition "A synthetic, lipophilic phenylpiperidine opioid agonist with analgesic and anesthetic properties. Fentanyl selectively binds to and activates the mu-receptor in the central nervous system (CNS) thereby mimicking the effects of endogenous opiates. Activation of the mu-subtype opioid receptor stimulates the exchange of GTP for GDP on the G-protein complex and subsequently inhibits adenylate cyclase. This causes a decrease in intracellular cAMP which inhibits cAMP-mediated calcium influx into the cell via the calcium channels and thereby results in hyperpolarization and reduced neuronal excitability." ;
          :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C494" ;
          rdfs:label "Fentanyl" .


:Ferritin :Synonyms "Ferritin" ;
          :definition "An iron protein complex, containing up to 23% iron, formed by the union of ferric iron with apoferritin; it is found in the intestinal mucosa, spleen, bone marrow, reticulocytes, and liver, and regulates iron storage and transport from the intestinal lumen to plasma." ;
          :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C16577" ;
          rdfs:label "Ferritin" .


