                                :definition "Pentraxin-related protein PTX3 (381 aa, ~42 kDa) is encoded by the human PTX3 gene. This protein is involved in both inflammation and complement recognition of pathogens." ;
                                :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C119682" ;
                                rdfs:label "Pentraxin-Related Protein PTX3" .


