2-[N-p'-Tolyl-N-(m'-hydroxyphenyl)aminomethyl]imidazoline
Phentolamine""" ;
              :definition "A synthetic imidazoline with alpha-adrenergic antagonist activity. As a competitive alpha-adrenergic antagonist, phentolamine binds to alpha-1 and alpha-2 receptors, resulting in a decrease in peripheral vascular resistance and vasodilatation. This agent also may block 5-hydroxytryptamine (5-HT) receptors and stimulate release of histamine from mast cells." ;
              :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C62066" ;
              rdfs:label "Phentolamine" .


