              :definition "A broad-spectrum semisynthetic, ampicillin-derived ureidopenicillin antibiotic. Piperacillin binds to penicillin binding proteins (PBP), the enzymes that catalyze the synthesis of peptidoglycan, a critical component of the bacterial cell wall. This blockade leads to the interruption of cell wall synthesis, consequently, leading to bacterial cell growth inhibition and cell lysis." ;
              :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C62069" ;
              rdfs:label "Piperacillin" .


