:Quinine :Synonyms """(-)-Quinine
QUIN
QUININE
Quinine""" ;
         :definition "A quinidine alkaloid isolated from the bark of the cinchona tree. Quinine has many mechanisms of action, including reduction of oxygen intake and carbohydrate metabolism; disruption of DNA replication and transcription via DNA intercalation; and reduction of the excitability of muscle fibers via alteration of calcium distribution. This agent also inhibits the drug efflux pump P-glycoprotein which is overexpressed in multi-drug resistant tumors and may improve the efficacy of some antineoplastic agents." ;
         :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C794" ;
         rdfs:label "Quinine" .


