                  :definition "A sulfonamide bacteriostatic antibiotic that is most commonly used in combination with trimethoprim as the drug Bactrim. Sulfamethoxazole competitively inhibits dihydropteroate synthase preventing the formation of dihydropteroic acid, a precursor of folic acid which is required for bacterial growth." ;
                  :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C47737" ;
                  rdfs:label "Sulfamethoxazole" .


