Zona Occludens Protein 1
TJP1
ZO-1
ZO1""" ;
                             :definition "Tight junction protein ZO-1 (1748 aa, ~195 kDa) is encoded by the human TJP1 gene. This protein plays a role in tight junction formation and signal transduction." ;
                             :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C114824" ;
                             rdfs:label "Tight Junction Protein ZO-1" .


:Tinidazole :Synonyms """Fasigyn
Simplotan
TDZ
TINIDAZOLE
Tindamax
Tinidazole
tinidazole""" ;
            :definition "A 5-nitroimidazole derivative with antiprotozoal property. Although the mechanism of action has not been fully elucidated, it has been suggested that tinidazole is metabolized and yields nitrite anions and metronidazole. Metronidazole's nitro group in turn is reduced via the parasite ferredoxin, thereby generating a series of free nitro radicals including nitro anions. Toxicity is achieved via depletion of sulfhydryl groups and DNA strand breaks with multiple hits having an additive effect and ultimately leading to cell death." ;
            :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C890" ;
            rdfs:label "Tinidazole" .


:Tirofiban :Synonyms """TIROFIBAN
Tirofiban""" ;
           :definition "A non-peptide tyrosine derivative, with anticoagulant activity. Upon administration, tirofiban antagonizes fibrinogen binding to the platelet cell surface receptor, glycoprotein (GP) IIb/IIIA complex, one of the two purinergic receptors activated by ADP. This prevents the GP IIb/IIIa receptor complex-mediated activation of adenylyl cyclase. This results in decreased levels of cAMP, interferes with the platelet membrane function and subsequent platelet-platelet interaction, prevents the release of platelet granule constituents and prolongs bleeding time." ;
           :reference "http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C76405" ;
           rdfs:label "Tirofiban" .


:Tissue_Factor :Synonyms """Tissue Thromboplastin
