Dopa, DL-
Dopamine""" ;
                                                                                   :definition "The racemic mixture of the precursor of dopamine L-DOPA (levodopa) and D-DOPA, with antiparkinsonian properties. L-DOPA is converted to dopamine by DOPA decarboxylase and can cross the blood-brain barrier (BBB). When in the brain, levodopa is decarboxylated to dopamine and stimulates the dopaminergic receptors, thereby compensating for the depleted supply of endogenous dopamine seen in Parkinson's disease." ;
